“probation  hostel”  means  a  hostel  established  or  appointed 
under  section  61  as  a  place  of  residence  for  children  required  to 
reside  there  under  sections  46  and  98;

(a)  to whom the care, custody and control of a child has been 
given by order of a Court under subparagraph 30(1)(c)(i); 
or;

(b)  permitted by the Protector under section 35 or 37, as the 
case  may  be,  to  receive  a  child  into  his  care,  custody 
and  control;

(c)  all  offences  under  the  *Internal  Security  Act  1960  
[Act  82]  punishable  with  imprisonment  for  life  or  with 
death;

(b)  in  relation  to  criminal  proceedings,  means  a  person 
who  has  attained  the  age  of  criminal  responsibility  as 
prescribed  in  section  82  of  the  Penal  Code  [Act  574];

“counsellor”  means  any  counsellor,  assistant  counsellor, 
psychology officer or assistant psychology officer in the Ministry 
responsible  for  welfare  services;

“Director General” means the Director General of Social Welfare 
and  includes  the  State  Director  of  Social  Welfare  of  each  of  the 
States;

“community  service”  means  any  work,  service  or  course  of 
instruction  for  the  betterment  of  the  public  at  large  under  the 
purview  of  the  Ministry  responsible  for  welfare  services;

“Social  Welfare  Officer”  means  any  Social  Welfare  Officer  in 
the  Ministry  or  Department  responsible  for  welfare  services  and 
includes  any Assistant  Social  Welfare  Officer;

“prostitution”  means  the  act  of  a  person  offering  that  person’s 
body  for  sexual  gratification  for  hire  whether  in  money  or  in 
kind;

(b)  in relation to places different parts of which are occupied 
by  different  persons,  means  the  respective  person  in 
occupation  or  control  of  each  part;

“Henry Gurney School order” means an order made by a Court 
For  Children  sending  a  child  aged  fourteen  years  or  above  to  a 
Henry  Gurney  School;

“brothel”  means  any  place  occupied  or  used  by  any  two  or 
more  persons  whether  at  the  same  time  or  at  different  times  for 
the  purpose  of  prostitution;

“relative” means a person who is related through full-blood or 
half-blood,  or  through  marriage  or  adoption,  including  de  facto 
adoption;

“place”  includes  any  building,  house,  office,  shop,  flat,  room 
or  cubicle  or  part  thereof,  any  open  or  enclosed  space,  and  any 
conveyance;

“place of assignation” means any place where communication is 
established with any child either directly or through intermediary 
for  purposes  of  prostitution;

(g)  to collect and collate data and information, and undertake 
and  promote  research,  relating  to  the  care,  protection, 
rehabilitation, development and participation of children;

(iii)  any other offence punishable with imprisonment, 
whether in itself only or in addition to or in lieu 
of  a  fine,  for  more  than  two  years;

(a)  shall  have  the  power  of  a  Magistrate  in  respect  of  the 
taking  of  evidence  at  any  inquiry  held  by  him  under 
this Act;

(c)  any child in respect of whom any offence under any written 
law  has  been  or  is  suspected  to  have  been  committed; 
or

(a)  the  child  has  been  or  there  is  substantial  risk  that  the 
child will be physically injured or emotionally injured or 
sexually  abused  by  his  parent  or  guardian  or  a  relative;

(d)  the  parent  or  guardian  of  the  child  has  neglected  or  is 
unwilling to provide for him adequate care, food, clothing 
and  shelter;

(ii)  has been abandoned by his parent or guardian and 
after reasonable inquiries the parent or guardian 
cannot  be  found;

(i)  begging or receiving alms, whether or not there 
is  any  pretence  of  singing,  playing,  performing 
or  offering  anything  for  sale;

(a)  order his parent or guardian to execute a bond to exercise 
proper  care  and  guardianship  for  a  period  specified  by 
the  Court  For  Children;

(b)  make  an  order  placing  the  child  in  the  custody  of  a  fit 
and  proper  person  for  a  period  specified  by  the  Court 
For  Children;

(ca)  make an order placing the child in a centre for a period of 
three years from the date of the order or until he attains 
the  age  of  eighteen  years,  whichever  is  the  shorter;

(a)  that the parent or guardian of the child accompanied by 
the  child  shall  attend  interactive  workshops  organized 
at  designated  centres  established  for  such  purpose;

(a)  begging,  receiving  alms,  whether  or  not  there  is  any 
pretence  of  singing,  playing,  performing  or  offering 
anything  for  sale;

(i)  in the care of a relative or fit and proper person 
on  such  terms  and  conditions  as  the  Protector 
may  require;

(i)  in the care of a relative or fit and proper person 
on  such  terms  and  conditions  as  the  Protector 
may  require;

(a)  is being induced to perform any sexual act, or is in any 
physical  or  social  environment  which  may  lead  to  the 
performance  of  such  act;

whether  or  not  for  the  purposes  of  prostitution  or  for 
having  sexual  intercourse  with  another  or  for  immoral 
purposes;

(d)  make an order placing the child in a centre for a period 
not  exceeding  three  years  from  the  date  of  the  order; 
or

(a)  the child is being threatened or intimidated for purposes of 
prostitution or for purposes of having sexual intercourse 
with  another  or  for  any  immoral  purpose;

(a)  that the parent or guardian of the child accompanied by 
the  child  shall  attend  interactive  workshops  organized 
at  designated  centres  established  for  such  purpose;

(b)  that  the  parent  or  guardian  of  the  child  shall  visit  the 
child on a regular basis as determined by the Protector; 
or

(b)  procures  a  child  for  purposes  of  prostitution  or  for  the 
purposes  of  having  sexual  intercourse  with  any  other 
person,  either  within  or  outside  Malaysia;

of  having  sexual  intercourse  with  any  other  person  or 
for immoral purposes, either within or outside Malaysia, 
and  with  intent  to  aid  such  purpose;

(a)  who  takes  or  causes  to  be  taken  into  a  brothel  a  child 
has  disposed  of  the  child  with  the  intent  or  knowledge 
mentioned  in  paragraph  43(1)(a);

(b)  who receives a child into a brothel or harbours a child in 
a  brothel  has  obtained  possession  of  the  child  with  the 
intent  or  knowledge  mentioned  in  paragraph  43(1)(a);

(a)  that  the  parent  or  guardian  of  the  child  shall  visit  the 
child on a regular basis as determined by the Court For 
Children;

(b)  that the parent or guardian of the child accompanied by 
the  child  shall  attend  interactive  workshops  organized 
at  designated  centres  established  for  such  purpose;

(A)  will not leave the area or the State in which 
he then is without the prior written consent 
of  the  Protector;

(ii)  has  taken  all  reasonable  steps  to  communicate 
with  the  other  person  but  has  been  unable  to 
communicate  with  him;

(c)  require any person who has information as to the child’s 
whereabouts to disclose that information to the authorized 
person;

(b)  knowingly assists or induces, directly or indirectly, a child 
to  escape  from  a  place  of  safety  or  a  place  of  refuge; 
or

(b)  the probation report submitted to the Court For Children 
shows that the child is in need of institutional rehabilitation; 
and

(a)  escapes from the approved school in which he is detained, 
or  from  any  hospital,  home  or  place  in  which  he  is 
receiving  medical  attention;

(i)  for  the  words  “approved  school”  wherever 
appearing  there  shall  be  substituted  the  words 
“Henry  Gurney  School”;

(a)  exercise in respect of the child all the powers which may 
be  exercised  under  this  Act  by  a  Court  For  Children; 
and

(b)  to  ensure  that  a  child,  if  a  girl,  while  being  so  detained 
or  conveyed,  or  waiting,  is  under  the  care  of  a  woman; 
and

(b)  discharge  the  child  upon  his  executing  a  bond  to  be  of 
good  behaviour  and  to  comply  with  such  conditions  as 
may  be  imposed  by  the  Court;

(b)  that the parent or guardian accompanied by the child shall 
attend  interactive  workshops  organized  at  designated 
centres  established  for  such  purpose;

(b)  shall  perform  the  community  service  for  the  number  of 
hours  in  aggregate  imposed  on  him  by  the  Court  For 
Children  within  the  period  not  exceeding  six  months;

(i)  that the child shall attend interactive workshops 
organized  at  designated  centres  established  for 
such  purpose;

(a)  consider the recommendations and views of a probation 
officer as to the suitability of the community service to 
be  performed  by  the  child;

(i)  that  the  probationer  shall  reside  at  a  probation 
hostel,  at  the  home  of  his  parent  or  guardian 
or  relative  or  at  some  other  place;

(ii)  that  the  probationer  shall  attend  an  educational 
institution to be recommended by the probation 
officer;

(a)  the  Court  shall  forthwith  give  sufficient  copies  of  the 
amending  or  discharging  order  to  the  probation  officer; 
and

(c)  remove by force any obstruction to entry, search, seizure, 
detention or removal as he is empowered to effect under 
subsection  (2);

(a)  provide  the  Protector  or  police  officer  with  all  such 
facilities  and  assistance  as  he  may  reasonably  require; 
and

(a)  refuses the Protector or Social Welfare Officer access to 
any premises, or fails to submit to a search by a person 
authorized  to  search  him  under  this Act;

(d)  omits, refuses or neglects to give to a Protector or Social 
Welfare Officer any information which may be reasonably 
required  of  him  and  which  he  is  empowered  to  give;

(a)  delivering the document to that person or by delivering 
the  document  at  the  last  known  place  of  residence 
of  that  person  to  an  adult  member  of  his  family;

(a)  to  prescribe  the  conduct,  management,  discipline  and 
control  of  approved  schools,  Henry  Gurney  Schools, 
probation  hostels,  places  of  detention  or  centres;

(i)  to  prescribe  the  selection  and  qualifications  of  fit  and 
proper  persons  with  whom  a  child  in  need  of  care  and 
protection  may  be  placed;

(n)  to prescribe the particulars, photographs or other means 
of  identification  to  be  furnished  in  relation  to  a  child 
in  need  of  protection;

(p)  to  prescribe  the  records  to  be  kept  in  respect  of  every 
child in need of protection and the manner in which the 
records  shall  be  kept;

(s)  to  prescribe  the  form  of  notices,  orders,  warrants, 
summonses  and  bonds  under  this  Act  and  the  manner 
of  service  thereof;

“repealed Acts”  means  the  Juvenile  Courts Act  1947  [Act  90], 
the Women and Girls Protection Act 1973 [Act 106] and the Child 
Protection Act  1991  [Act  468]  repealed  under  this Act;
